  "prompt": "Why should I learn phrasal verbs?",
  "response": "Learning phrasal verbs is important for several reasons:\n\n1. Natural communication\n- Native English speakers use phrasal verbs frequently in everyday conversation\n- They make your English sound more fluent and authentic\n\n2. Improved comprehension\n- Many phrasal verbs have meanings that can't be understood by their individual words\n- Understanding them helps you better comprehend spoken and written English\n\n3. Language flexibility\n- Phrasal verbs allow you to express ideas more precisely and concisely\n- They provide more nuanced ways of communicating\n\n4. Enhanced vocabulary\n- Phrasal verbs expand your vocabulary beyond basic verb-noun combinations\n- They help you express complex ideas more eloquently\n\n5. Better writing and speaking skills\n- Using phrasal verbs makes your language more dynamic and engaging\n- They help you sound more like a native speaker\n\n6. Practical in various contexts\n- Used in informal conversations, professional settings, literature, and media\n- Essential for business, academic, and social communication\n\n7. Cultural understanding\n- Phrasal verbs often reflect cultural nuances and idiomatic expressions\n- Learning them helps you better understand English-speaking cultures\n\n8. Improved language proficiency\n- Mastering phrasal verbs is a sign of advanced English skills\n- They are typically more challenging for language learners",
